data.description: Your new home has SOLAR PANELS, which help lower the costs of your monthly utility bills. Lovely 3 bedroom ranch with 2 full baths on the main level. Over 1400 sq feet on the main floor and an additional 1400 sq feet in the solid and dry unfinished basement awaits your design and finishing touches. The fenced in yard is the perfect place to play and keep your beloved pets secure. The covered patio is a great place to enjoy the outdoors and BBQ, no matter the weather. The formal living room captures the brick fireplace which creates a peaceful, relaxing and quiet conversation space to gather around and stay warm during these cold winter months. The family room has beautiful bay windows with built in blinds and when they are open they let so much natural light pour into the room. The family room has sliding glass doors that open onto a small deck leading to the patio which can also be accessed through the garage. The eat in Kitchen is very spacious with plenty of cabinets, granite countertops, gas stove, fridge, dishwasher and microwave which will all stay with the home. The kitchen is large enough for an oversized table and chairs with additional countertop seating. The master bedroom has its own private full bathroom with a stand up shower, which is so hard to find. Hardwood floors throughout the living room, hall and all three bedrooms. The brand new Davidson School Elementary School is close by and one of their public playgrounds is located right across the street. The Sellers said the park right across the street was perfect because they would sit on their front  porch and watch their kids play for hours. Your new home is just minutes away from several different grocery stores, gyms, coffee shops, home improvement stores with quick access to I69, I-35 and I-29
